The paper discusses a dimensionality reduction technique that is commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications. The use of GPUs is a key aspect of the algorithm design, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the categories of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper involves mathematical algorithms and computational geometry, which could potentially place it in the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
